data.text: 11429 Demodokus is a mid-sized Jupiter trojan from the Greek camp, approximately 38 kilometers (24 miles) in diameter. It was discovered during the Palomar–Leiden survey at the Palomar Observatory in 1960 and later named after the blind singer Demodocus from Greek mythology.[1] The dark Jovian asteroid has a longer-than average rotation period of 50.2 hours.[6]
